    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>Hi,</p>

<p>When you create Zend_Dojo_Form_Element_Editor in a Zend_Dojo_Form and try to use $form-&gt;getValue('editor') it works different in Firefox and other browsers.</p>

<p>This is the code in to create the element:
 $messagetoparents = new Zend_Dojo_Form_Element_Editor('bericht',array(
            'required'   =&gt; false,
            'label'      =&gt; Zend_Registry::get('Zend_Translate')-&gt;translate("Berichtje"),
            'style'    =&gt; 'width: 35em; height: 10em;',
        ));
        $this-&gt;addElement($messagetoparents);</p>

<p>To retrieve the value it acts different in Firefox( 3.5.5) seems to work fine in safari and IE.</p>

<p>To retrieve the value in any other browser you would use $form-&gt;getValue('editor');
In Firefox you have to do $value = $form-&gt;getValue('editor'); $value['Editor'] the getValue returns an array in Firefox.</p>

